# Implementation Plan — Tailwind CSS Migration

This plan outlines the design system and steps to migrate the Trip Budget Tracker UI from CSS Modules to pure Tailwind CSS utility classes, implementing a unified, responsive dark-mode-first aesthetic with glassmorphism cards and HSL tokens.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Dark Mode by Default:** The application theme will change to a dark slate background (`bg-slate-950` / `hsl(222 47% 8%)`) with light typography (`text-slate-100`). Cards will utilize semi-transparent glassmorphism styling (`bg-slate-900/40 backdrop-blur-xl border border-slate-800/80`).
> 
> **CSS Module Deletion:** All `.module.css` and `.css` (except `index.css`) files will be deleted upon successful migration to keep the codebase clean.

